<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="121" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">857.0011/93: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-31">August 31,
                                1940</date>.<lb/>[Received August 31—9:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>From Schoenfeld, Norwegian series No. 2, 31st. The King of Norway
                            summoned me this morning and requested that following message be
                            conveyed to the President: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“I am deeply grateful to you for all you are doing for the Crown
                                    Princess. Both I and the Crown Prince assure you of our deep
                                    thanks and our very warm regards.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed> [Schoenfeld] <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>